# FORMA — LegalTech SaaS Platform
## Deployment & Setup Guide

---

## 📁 File Structure

```
forma/
├── index.html              ← Full frontend (single file)
├── backend/
│   └── Code.gs             ← Google Apps Script backend
└── README.md               ← This file
```

---

## 🚀 Step 1: Setup Google Sheets

1. Go to [sheets.google.com](https://sheets.google.com) → Create new spreadsheet
2. Name it **"FORMA Database"**
3. Copy the **Sheet ID** from the URL:
   ```
   https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/[THIS_IS_YOUR_SHEET_ID]/edit
   ```

---

## 🗂 Step 2: Setup Google Drive Folder

1. Go to [drive.google.com](https://drive.google.com) → New → Folder
2. Name it **"FORMA Uploads"**
3. Right-click the folder → Get link → Copy folder ID from URL:
   ```
   https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/[THIS_IS_YOUR_FOLDER_ID]
   ```
4. Share the folder so the script can write to it

---

## ⚙️ Step 3: Deploy Google Apps Script

1. Open your Google Sheet → **Extensions → Apps Script**
2. Delete existing code → Paste entire contents of `backend/Code.gs`
3. Update the config at the top:
   ```javascript
   const SHEET_ID = 'paste-your-sheet-id-here';
   const DRIVE_FOLDER_ID = 'paste-your-folder-id-here';
   const ADMIN_EMAIL = 'your-email@domain.com';
   ```
4. **Run** `initializeSheets()` once (click the function dropdown → Run)
   - Grant required permissions when prompted
5. **Deploy → New Deployment**:
   - Type: **Web App**
   - Execute as: **Me**
   - Who has access: **Anyone**
   - Click **Deploy**
6. Copy the **Deployment URL** — it looks like:
   ```
   https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycb.../exec
   ```

---

## 🔗 Step 4: Connect Frontend

1. Open `index.html` in a text editor
2. Find line near top of `<script>`:
   ```javascript
   const APPS_SCRIPT_URL = 'https://script.google.com/macros/s/YOUR_SCRIPT_ID/exec';
   ```
3. Replace with your actual deployment URL from Step 3

---

## 🌐 Step 5: Deploy Frontend

### Option A: GitHub Pages (Free)
1. Create a GitHub repository
2. Upload `index.html` to the repo root
3. Settings → Pages → Source: main branch
4. Your site: `https://username.github.io/repository-name`

### Option B: Netlify (Free, Custom Domain)
1. Go to [netlify.com](https://netlify.com)
2. Drag & drop the `forma/` folder
3. Get instant URL + custom domain support

### Option C: Vercel (Free)
1. Install Vercel CLI: `npm i -g vercel`
2. Run `vercel` in the `forma/` directory

### Option D: Traditional Hosting
- Upload `index.html` to any web server (cPanel, AWS S3, etc.)

